\chapter{Command-Line Interface}
\label{cli}

The [[learnlog]] command lets teachers and teaching assistants
review the development logs that students produce.
It provides three subcommands: [[git]] forwards Git commands to
the log repository, [[export]] creates a portable bundle
of the log, and [[play]] gives an interactive viewer for browsing
the commit history.

We use Typer for the CLI framework because it gives us type-checked
arguments with minimal boilerplate, and the modern
[[Annotated]] style makes the parameter declarations self-documenting.


