\section{Finding the learnlog directory}

When the user runs [[learnlog play]] or [[learnlog export]] without
specifying a directory, we need to find the [[.learnlog/]] directory.
We walk up from the current directory, mirroring how Git itself
searches for [[.git/]].
This means the user can run the command from a subdirectory of their
project and it will still work.

<<helper functions>>=
def find_learnlog_dir(start=None):
    """Walk up from ``start`` to find a ``.learnlog/`` directory.

    Returns the directory containing ``.learnlog/``, or ``None``
    if no learnlog repository is found.
    """
    path = pathlib.Path(start or os.getcwd()).resolve()
    while True:
        if (path / ".learnlog").is_dir():
            return path
        parent = path.parent
        if parent == path:
            return None
        path = parent
@

